&s;ilence, and a gloomy dread of im|pending terrors.</P> 
<P>"Leaving this &s;eat of de&s;olation, we pro|&s;ecuted our
voyage along the coa&s;ts; and the next day came to Rochetta, where we landed,
although the earth &s;till continued in violent agitations. But we were
&s;carce arrived at our inn, when we were once more obliged to return to the
